        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 8:28PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 826 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 4 miles
northeast of Blanco, moving east at 25 mph. Other strong
thunderstorms were located along a line from 5 southwest of Ashland
to 10 miles souhteast of Blanco moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Mcalester...                      Pittsburg...
Kiowa...                          Haywood...
Dow...                            Bache...
Hartshorne...                     Haileyville...
Mcalester Regional Airport...     Krebs...
Alderson...                       Blanco...
Ashland...                        Savanna...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for southeastern
Oklahoma.</instruction>
